            <head><ref target="https://github.com/raffazizzi/TEIditto">TEIditto</ref> - a JS library for NoXSL TEI publishing</head>
            <p>This idea is much indebted to <ref target="http://dcl.ils.indiana.edu/teibp/">TEI Boilerplate</ref>, but avoids the XSLT step.</p>
            <p>The TEI is registered as HTML5 elements using the <ref target="https://github.com/raffazizzi/TEIditto">TEIditto</ref> library. 
               Registering TEI as HTML5 is an idea taken from an <ref target="https://github.com/hcayless/appcrit">online critical apparatus prototype</ref> by Hugh Cayless.</p>
            <p>
               Here's how this page works: 
               <list type="instructions" rend="numbered">
                  <item>TEIditto loads a TEI XML file and registers it as HTML5</item>
                  <item>Users can use TEIditto to register custom behaviors</item>
                  <item>A CSS styles the TEI for display (the current CSS comes from TEI Boilerplate)</item>
               </list>
            </p>
            <p>See <ref target="readme.xml">this document</ref> as XML.</p>
         </div>
